# bad_from
# ========
# One Perl regular expression per line, matched against sender identity fields.
# The exact string may include a display name and angle-bracket address.
# Matching is normally case-insensitive in Cleanfeed's processing path.
#
# Exact bare address:
# ^abuse-campaign-2026@example\.invalid$
#
# Exact display name with optional whitespace before the address:
# ^Campaign Bot\s*<bot@example\.invalid>$
#
# Either a bare address or the same address inside angle brackets:
# (?:^|<)bot@example\.invalid(?:>|$)
#
# Generated local parts with exactly six decimal digits:
# ^promo-[0-9]{6}@spam-domain\.example$
#
# A bounded family with an optional plus tag:
# ^campaign(?:\+[A-Za-z0-9_-]{1,24})?@example\.invalid$
#
# Literal plus signs must be escaped (\+).  Dots in domains must also be
# escaped (\.).  Never block gmail.com, outlook.com, a common surname, or a
# generic display word: this list causes direct rejection.
